    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-07T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="567"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9963: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-07T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 7, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 7—12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Embassy was informed yesterday by the Minister of Foreign Affairs that “The
                    Chinese Government has, in view of the present tense situation, closed to
                    navigation the mouth of the Min Kiang, in <pb facs="0460" n="452"
                        xml:id="pg_452"/> Fukien Province, and that all shipping through that place
                    has been suspended as from September 4”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
